OL,3,C'Heartbreaking' memories of Miners'
OL,4,CStrike pulled together for 40th
OL,5,Canniversary
OL,7,F"We wanted to tell those stories but,
OL,8,Falso, redress the balance a little bit
OL,9,Fthis time by hearing from some of the
OL,10,Fmen and their families who didn't go
OL,11,Fon strike and the impact that had on
OL,12,Fthem and how they were treated in
OL,13,Ftheir communities but, also, the
OL,14,Fminers who went back early.
OL,16,F"We're all familiar with the stories
OL,17,Fof people struggling to put food on
OL,18,Fthe table, to pay their mortgages,
OL,19,Fetc. And some people did feel the
OL,20,Fpressure, as the strike went on, to go
OL,21,Fback to work early."
