OL,3,C'Heartbreaking' memories of Miners'
OL,4,CStrike pulled together for 40th
OL,5,Canniversary
OL,7,FThe strike began after the National
OL,8,FCoal Board announced in March 1984
OL,9,Fthat 20 pits would close with the loss
OL,10,Fof 20,000 jobs.
OL,12,FIt lasted for a year and was mired in
OL,13,Fconflict ` especially when the
OL,14,FNottinghamshire miners refused to
OL,15,Ffollow colleagues in areas like
OL,16,FYorkshire and South Wales out on
OL,17,Fstrike.
OL,19,FThere was violence on picket lines as
OL,20,Fthousands of police from all over the
OL,21,FUK were ferried into the coalfields.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G7/12
